    "body": "<p>It's easy to maintain a good git practice now with the help of agentic engineering - just ask the AI to clean up and stage changes for you.</p>\n<p>The mechanics of git – staging, writing commit messages, rebasing – is now cheap.</p>\n<p>But the disciplines that make git history a valuable source of data(<span class=\"wikilink-plain\">Disciplines of clean git practice</span>, <span class=\"wikilink-plain\">A rich git history is a treasure trove for debugging with AI</span>) still requires good human judgement. For instance, you have to want atomic commits before AI can help you make them.</p>\n<p>One thing I do that helps is <span class=\"wikilink-plain\">Bake in git discipline as agent instructions to preserve it</span>.</p>"
