    "lede": "Open-source SDK that enables easy integration of AI models into agents that can use NLP to complete tasks and collaborate with other agents.",
    "body": "<p>Open-source SDK that enables easy integration of AI models into agents that can use NLP to complete tasks and collaborate with other agents.</p>\n<h3>Core components</h3>\n<ul><li>Agents - out of the box agents with tool calling, multi-turn conversations with history, structured outputs and streaming from an interface that enables multi-agent orchestration</li><li>Chat providers - abstraction layer for using many different AI service providers</li><li>Function tools - MCP, custom tools that enhances agent's capability and integrate with external APIs and services</li><li>Built-in tools - prebuilt, code interpreter, file search and web search</li><li>Conversation management - role-based messaging systems for persistent conversation format across interactions</li><li>Workflow orchestration - create workflows, group chat and hand off pattern for multi-agent orchestration</li></ul>\n<p>MAF is aimed to streamlines the creation of agents and multi-agent workflow.</p>\n<p>Without MAF, we would be building those features from scratch. <em>What does this look like in practice?</em></p>\n<p><em>When do we not use it?</em> There are dozens of other Agent SDKs in the wild, MAF is recommendable if your agentic setup is powered by Azure.</p>\n<p><em>What does this connect to?</em></p>"
