    "lede": "I used to think that I must use complicated sounding words to show my competence - wordmaxxing.",
    "body": "<p>I used to think that I must use complicated sounding words to show my competence - wordmaxxing. I remember writing down scientific words used in research papers to memorize them with cards(spaced repetition).</p>\n<p>The outcome is always the same - I lose steam after day 2 and give up. I learned later that people use complicated word as a thin veil to conceal the void of understanding. It's a clear sign that they themselves don't know what they are talking about.</p>\n<p>This is rampant in the consulting world, people talk with such confidence that hides their shallow thinking. From my experience in consulting, more jargons means more obvious that they don't know what they're talking about.</p>\n<p>In politics, English is used in a tool to manipulate uncomfortable facts. See Orwell's essay on politics and English.</p>"
