    "body": "<p>Use Y-statement to quickly capture low stake decisions that don't require a full MADR. It's fast due to it strictly being limited to a single sentence.(Also known as Why-Statement) Especially useful when speed matters more than detailed rationale, e.g. in a Proof of Concept.</p>\n<p>This is the template:</p>\n<p>In the context of &lt;use case and/or component&gt; facing &lt;non-functional concern&gt;, we decided for &lt;option&gt; and neglected &lt;options&gt; to achieve &lt;quality&gt;, accepting downside &lt;consequence&gt;.</p>"
